## **Agent checklist**

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 | Load `GH_TOKEN` + `gh auth setup-git` + `GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY` |
| 2 | Commit/push work branch (secret scan) |
| 3 | `git fetch`; sync deploy branch to work (`reset --hard` or ref push) |
| 4 | Push work + deploy branches |
| 5 | Verify Amplify jobs + GH Actions |
| 6 | If Amplify FAILED with `build output ... exceeds ... 230686720` → apply **Workaround E** (WEB_COMPUTE 220 MiB cap) |
| 7 | Report table: repo, branch, SHA, build status, blockers |

**BLOCKERS:** auth failure, merge conflicts, ref push not fast-forward, push rejected on protected branch without bypass, Amplify WEB_COMPUTE artifact > 220 MiB (see Workaround E).

---

## **Anti-patterns**

- ❌ Push feature branch only and assume prod deployed
- ❌ Run `gh auth login` without clearing/conflicting `GH_TOKEN` when token already works
- ❌ Skip deploy-branch push for Amplify/ECS repos
- ❌ Commit `ordered_PROD.sql` or `.env*` during deploy prep
- ❌ Local `reset --hard` on mosc-temp while SQL file is locked — use **ref push** instead
- ❌ Assume Amplify deploy succeeded because `[prune-amplify]` reported under 220 MB — WEB_COMPUTE bundle can be ~58 MB larger (Workaround E)

